<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Male.</emphasis>
Pereopods 1-3 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Xangoniscus loboi sp. nov. Male A uropod B pereopod 1 C pereopod 2 D pereopod 3 E pereopod 4 F pereopod 5 G pereopod 6 H pereopod 7." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.42.75725.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/632546" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">10B-D</figureCitation>
) merus with proximal lobe bearing fringed scales and fine setae on sternal margin. Pereopods 4-6 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Xangoniscus loboi sp. nov. Male A uropod B pereopod 1 C pereopod 2 D pereopod 3 E pereopod 4 F pereopod 5 G pereopod 6 H pereopod 7." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.42.75725.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/632546" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">10E-G</figureCitation>
) merus with dense field of short setae on sternal margin. Pereopod 6 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Xangoniscus loboi sp. nov. Male A uropod B pereopod 1 C pereopod 2 D pereopod 3 E pereopod 4 F pereopod 5 G pereopod 6 H pereopod 7." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.42.75725.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/632546" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">10G</figureCitation>
) merus bearing brush of setae on sternal margin. Pereopod 7 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Xangoniscus loboi sp. nov. Male A uropod B pereopod 1 C pereopod 2 D pereopod 3 E pereopod 4 F pereopod 5 G pereopod 6 H pereopod 7." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.42.75725.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/632546" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">10H</figureCitation>
) ischium straight on sternal margin, merus, and carpus with no distinct modifications. Genital papilla (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Xangoniscus loboi sp. nov. Male A genital papilla B pleopod 1 C Pleopod 2 D pleopod 3 exopod E pleopod 4 exopod F Pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.42.75725.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/632547" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">11A</figureCitation>
) lanceolate, enlarged on median portion, apical part narrow and pointed. Pleopod 1 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Xangoniscus loboi sp. nov. Male A genital papilla B pleopod 1 C Pleopod 2 D pleopod 3 exopod E pleopod 4 exopod F Pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.42.75725.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/632547" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">11B</figureCitation>
) exopod subtriangular, longer than wide, inner and outer margins bearing fringe of fine setae; endopod slightly longer than exopod, narrow basal article and flagelliform distal article; basipod with stout and broadly rounded medial part bearing fringe of fine setae along outer and distal margins. Pleopod 2 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Xangoniscus loboi sp. nov. Male A genital papilla B pleopod 1 C Pleopod 2 D pleopod 3 exopod E pleopod 4 exopod F Pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.42.75725.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/632547" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">11C</figureCitation>
) exopod triangular, median portion narrower, distal margin almost straight bearing three setae; endopod of two thickset articles, second article about three times as long as first, with complex apical part: distal margin rounded with two narrow transverse processes, subapical circular lobe strongly folded. Pleopod 3 exopod (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Xangoniscus loboi sp. nov. Male A genital papilla B pleopod 1 C Pleopod 2 D pleopod 3 exopod E pleopod 4 exopod F Pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.42.75725.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/632547" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">11D</figureCitation>
) triangular, slightly longer than wide, covering pleopods 1 and 2, bearing many short setae on distal margin. Pleopod 4 exopod (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Xangoniscus loboi sp. nov. Male A genital papilla B pleopod 1 C Pleopod 2 D pleopod 3 exopod E pleopod 4 exopod F Pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.42.75725.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/632547" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">11E</figureCitation>
) subrectangular, wider than long, distal portion bearing many short setae. Pleopod 5 exopod (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Xangoniscus loboi sp. nov. Male A genital papilla B pleopod 1 C Pleopod 2 D pleopod 3 exopod E pleopod 4 exopod F Pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.42.75725.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/632547" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">11F</figureCitation>
) subtrapezoidal, distal margin rounded bearing many short setae.
</paragraph>
